-- Koruna Weakens First Time in Four Days on Waning Spain Optimism
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-06-11T15:26:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-11/koruna-weakens-first-time-in-four-days-on-waning-spain-optimism.html
The Czech koruna depreciated 0.4
percent to 25.520 per euro by 5:07 p.m. in  Prague  as European
stocks erased most of today’s gains on mounting concern that a
bailout for Spanish banks won’t stop the euro-area debt crisis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
